The paper discusses multi-view representation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining. The paper covers both alignment and fusion approaches, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The paper also discusses generative models and neural network-based methods, which are popular in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
